This memorandum, addressed to the Secretary of State, delegates the authority under section 506(a)(1) of the Foreign Assistance Act of 1961 to direct the drawdown of up to $400 million in defense articles and services, as well as military education and training, to provide assistance to Ukraine. The Secretary of State is also authorized to make the necessary determinations required under this section to carry out the drawdown. The memorandum is signed by President Joseph R. Biden Jr. and directs that it be published in the Federal Register.